<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-09-08T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-09-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="844" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d844">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 711.5914/139</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the <gloss type="to">Danish Minister</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-09-08">
                                        <hi rend="italic">September 8, 1916</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>The treaty which was signed in New York ceding the Danish West Indies
                                to the United States was ratified by the Senate last night by a
                                majority of about six to one. No modification was made in the text
                                of the treaty.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Lansing</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>